WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified reference for ISO/AWI 19264‑2, which defines methods for
analysing imaging system quality in cultural heritage documentation.

WHY IT EXISTS
Cultural heritage imaging demands extreme colour accuracy and geometric
fidelity. GIOP includes this standard to guarantee that museum‑grade
captures can be processed and archived within its pipeline.

HOW IT WORKS
The standard specifies resolution measurement, colour accuracy using
CIEDE2000, geometric distortion limits, and uniformity requirements.
GIOP adopts these as the baseline for its “Level A – Certified Golden”
validation of heritage digitisation.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- Museum and archive digitisation.
- High‑resolution texture capture for VFX assets.

WHO USES IT
L3 Colorists and L2 Engineers working on heritage projects.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Provides an internationally accepted quality benchmark that GIOP can
certify against, ensuring digitised heritage is archivally sound.

